concept("gray",|std:///experiments/RascalTutor/Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/ColorModel/gray/gray.concept|,[],[],{"Library"},{},"","",""," \<ol\>\<li\> \<code\>Color gray(int g)\</code\>\</li\>\n\<li\> \<code\>Color gray(int g, real alpha)\</code\>\</li\>\n\<li\> \<code\>Color gray(real perc)\</code\>\</li\>\n\<li\> \<code\>Color gray(real prec, real alpha)\</code\>\</li\>\n\</ol\>",{}," Create gray colors in various shades:\n \<ol\>\<li\> Create a gray color between black (0) and white (255).\</li\>\n\<li\> Create a gray color between black (0) and white (255) with transparency \<code\>alpha\</code\>.\</li\>\n\<li\> Create a gray color between black (0.0) and white (1.0).\</li\>\n\<li\> Create a gray color between black (0.0) and white (1.0) transparency \<code\>alpha\</code\>.\</li\>\n\</ol\>"," Setting gray values with an integer in the range [0,255]:\n \<pre class=\"listing\"\>b1 = box(fillColor(gray(0)));\nb2 = box(fillColor(gray(125)));\nb3 = box(fillColor(gray(255)));\nrender(hcat([b1, b2, b3], size(50)));\n\</pre\> gives: \<img  alt=\"h1\" src=\"Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/ColorModel/gray/h1.png\"\>\n \<br/\>\n\<br/\>\n\n Setting gray values with an a percentage in the range [0.0, 1.0]:\n \<pre class=\"listing\"\>b1 = box(fillColor(gray(0.0)));\nb2 = box(fillColor(gray(0.5)));\nb3 = box(fillColor(gray(1.0)));\nrender(hcat([b1, b2, b3], size(50)));\n\</pre\> gives: \<img  alt=\"h2\" src=\"Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/ColorModel/gray/h2.png\"\>\n \<br/\>\n\<br/\>\n\n Setting transparency:\n \<pre class=\"listing\"\>b1 = box(fillColor(gray(0.5, 0.0)));\nb2 = box(fillColor(gray(0.5, 0.5)));\nb3 = box(fillColor(gray(0.5, 1.0)));\nrender(hcat([b1, b2, b3], size(50)));\n\</pre\> gives: \<img  alt=\"h3\" src=\"Courses/Rascal/Libraries/Vis/Figure/ColorModel/gray/h3.png\"\>\n","","",[])